               <p>I saw the prisoner take the great coat off the box of the last witness Sewell on Sunday was sennight at night, and he ran away, and<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="178210160040"></xptr> I ran after him, he dropped if, and a gentleman stopped him; I saw him drop it, and he was secured. The coat was taken up and kept in the possession of the owner, he has it now. The coat produced. </p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>The coat was laying on the ground when I crossed the highway, this man crossed and asked me where I got it, and I told him I picked it up. I am a <rs id="t17821016-24-deflabel135" type="occupation">sugar baker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17821016-24-defend258 t17821016-24-deflabel135"></join>; I have no friends here, they did not know I should be tried to-night.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17821016-24-verdict136" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17821016-24-verdict136" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
